Hong Kong Plans HK$12 Billion Railway for New Business District

-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 
2011-10-13T20:25:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/hong-kong-plans-hk-12-billion-railway-for-new-business-district.html
Hong Kong ’s government wants to
build a HK$12 billion ($1.5 billion) elevated monorail system in
the city’s planned new business district in Kowloon East,
Secretary for Development Carrie Lam said.  The 9-kilometer (5.6-mile), 12-station line will link
planned business commercial projects in the Kai Tak area with
the Hoi Bun Road and Kwun Tong Ferry developments, Lam said,
according to a government press release distributed yesterday.
The project is scheduled for completion in 2023, she said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  